description.narrative: Adolescent girls and boys, parents and community leaders have increased knowledge of and capacity to prevent and respond to child rights violations, including child marriage., which contributes to Access To Justice, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children, especially adolescent girls, in vulnerable regions are better protected from violence, abuse, exploitation and harmful practices, including in emergency situations

description.narrative: UNICEF strongly invested in the tailoring of messages and communication tools to address social norms and harmful traditional practices such a gender-based violence and child marriage but also to promote birth registration. Informing and sensitizing communities, parents, adolescents and children has been a major part of the child protection programme. Main channels targeted to spread the messages were both traditional and community leaders, adolescents and youth. Both have also been capacitated as duty-bearers to become child protection actors equipped to share information on and identify and refer children and women to child protection social services. | Status:Met | As-of Date:02/02/2022
